  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Programme of Support in the Prevention of Conflicts and Violent Extremism in the Border Areas of Benin, Burkina Faso and Togo</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the project is to contribute to improving the resilience of the populations of the cross-border areas of Benin, Burkina Faso and Togo that are at risk of community conflicts and violent extremism. The project aims to contribute, through a cross-border approach, to the establishment of an environment where women and young people can benefit from a better protection and are sufficiently involved in the mechanisms of local dialogue while enjoying viable economic opportunities. The project is the first cross-border initiative common to the three countries concerned and responds to the common threat of community conflicts and violent extremism.</narrative>
  </description>
